\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 Motivation is another statistic.\par
It is the desire to do things, and it matches the level of identity. Having it too low can kill the game, having it too high lowers happiness, possibly ending the game that way.        \par
It is about the desire. pushing forward toward all kind of actions. It is set by identity,which the higher it gets, the stronger the motivation is fueled. It is a 300-700-1000 basis as well, and it depends on identity level. Each identity level creates one for motivation.\par
The scope of the game is to kill this meter at the right time, when you feel like having an end. This can be done in multiple ways. One way, is to erode your identity, to take actions that surrender your personality in exchange forr a potential happiness. Other accidental way is being unhappy for a longer period, drawing out identity. \par
The other way, is by achieving your goals, in such way, that by raising happiness, youi can match the level of motivation in you, so that it can take it down and end the game in a preferred position in life.\par
It is a 0-1000 bar with own modifiers. It cannot be influenced directly, except in a psych ward  via medication. The psych ward affects identity, but also motivation thus, indirectly and directly.\par
Motivation stops growing if identity is low enough.\par
Motivation kills the game if under 0, and under 300 it begins locking out some actions.\par
If motivation is higher than happiness, it will harm happiness in time.\par
